In [19]:
# Random Sample Imputation
def randomsample_imputation(df, variable):
    df[variable] = df[variable]
    random_sample = df[variable].dropna().sample(df[variable].isnull().sum(), random_state=0)
    ##pandas need to have same index in order to merge the dataset
    random_sample.index = df[df[variable].isnull()].index
    df.loc[df[variable].isnull(), variable] = random_sample

# function to detect the outliers and repalace the values with upper and lower bounds
def detect_outlier(df, variable):
    quantile1, quantile3 = np.percentile(df[variable],[25,75])
    IQR = quantile3 - quantile1                  #IQR=df.MinTemp.quantile(0.75)-df.MinTemp.quantile(0.25)
    lower_bridge = quantile1 - IQR*1.5           # df[variable].quantile(0.25) - IQR*1.5
    upper_bridge = quantile3 + IQR*1.5           # df[variable].quantile(0.75) + IQR*1.5
    
    #Replacing Outliers in Column with a upper and Lower boundary value
    df.loc[df[variable] >= upper_bridge, variable] = upper_bridge
    df.loc[df[variable] <= lower_bridge, variable] = lower_bridge
